Q6 - Signal Sender and Receiver

This project contains two programs:
- signal_receiver: Receives a byte value (0-255) through signals (SIGUSR1 and SIGUSR2).
- signal_sender: Sends a byte value (0-255) to the receiver using signals.

How to compile:
    gcc -Wall -Wextra -o signal_receiver signal_receiver.c
    gcc -Wall -Wextra -o signal_sender signal_sender.c

How to run:
1. Start ./signal_receiver and note its PID.
2. Run ./signal_sender and input the receiver's PID and a number (0-255) to send.
